<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
<link type="text/css" href="styles.css" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
main {
   max-width: 45em;
   margin-inline: auto;
}
#reports {
	text-align: center;
}
#reports h2 {
	border-image-outset: 0;
	text-align: center;
}
#reports h2 [href] {
	display: block;
	color: inherit;
	text-underline-offset: 0.15em;
}
#reports, #reports details div {
	display: grid;
	grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
	grid-gap: 0 2em;
}
#reports details, #reports summary {
	grid-column: 1/-1;
}
#reports details ul {
	margin: 0;
	padding: 0;
	list-style: none;
}
#reports details ul:nth-of-type(1) {
	grid-column: 1;
}
#reports details ul:nth-of-type(2) {
	grid-column: 2;
}
#reports details ul li {
	margin-inline: 0;
}
#reports details ul li [href] {
	display: block;
}
#reports details ul li [href]:hover {
	background: silver;
}
</style>
<title>BCD Watch</title>
</head>
<body>

  <main>
    <h1>Welcome to BCD-Watch</h1>
    <div id="reports">
    <div>
      <h2><a href="weekly">Weekly Report</a></h2>
      <p>All the BCD updates that occurred in the last week: features added or removed, and which features gained or lost engine support.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
      <h2><a href="weekly-completed">New Baselines Weekly Report</a></h2>
      <p>All the BCD entries that moved to “baseline” status in the past week; i.e., are now supported in all three major browser engines.
      </p>
      </div>
      <details>
        <summary>
          Full index of past reports
        </summary>
        <div>
        <ul>
	{{#each weekly}}
		<li><a href="weekly/{{this}}">{{stripFileExtension this}}</a></li>
	{{/each}}
        </ul>
        <ul>
	{{#each completed}}
		<li><a href="weekly-completed/{{this}}">{{stripFileExtension this}}</a></li>
	{{/each}}
        </ul>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
    <p>This site automatically collects, indexes, and makes available for viewing (and as subscribe-able feeds), information about updates to <a href="https://github.com/mdn/browser-compat-data">Browser Compatibility Data (BCD)</a>. Currently there are two different views (and feeds) on this data, which are compiled each Tuesday (US/Eastern time).</p>
    <p>Perhaps you're interested in <a href="weekly/index.html">which changes were reported last week</a>, or more specifically <a href="weekly-completed/index.html">which features became "new baseline" last week</a> (marked as available in all 3 engines).</p>
  </main>
</body>
</html>
